FROM: https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms229042(v=vs.110).aspx

When writing an API it's important that designers are consistent. If we use a programming model that is actually independent of programming language then our APIs can be consistent and easy to use.

The terms: Do, Consider, Avoid and Do not prefix the recommendations that are used here. These guidelines are intended to help class library designers understand the trade offs between different solutions.

